## M4.5a: dropping a borrow binding must release the underlying borrow.
##
## After `-r`, the read borrow on `user` is gone, so `w = !user` (write
## borrow) must be allowed. Without the fix, the checker leaves
## `user.read_borrows` non-zero and rejects the write.
##
## EXPECTED: clean (no diagnostics).

sub main()
  user = User(name: "Steve")
  r = ?user
  -r
  w = !user
